```
Article 5 (Amendments):
If it is seen that this constitution is not fit to fully serve the needs of the association — I.E. Grammar or needs addition — then the process to modify this document can thusly be enacted. The rules of such modifications are such: (1) All members, present in said meeting or not, must agree to pursue such modification. (2) The change, addition, or removal must be specific and acute, so it can thusly be approved by all members.
```